I can't wait for us to be married, either.

144
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:11,542
That's why I have to finish my book,

145
00:10:11,625 --> 00:10:12,458
you see?

146
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:14,792
Yes.

147
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:17,167
Yes!

148
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:20,292
Listen, darling, my train is leaving.

149
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:21,917
Hugs and kisses.

150
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:25,125
Yes.

151
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,875
Listen, I'll call you back
as soon as possible.

152
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:29,875
Love you, bye.

153
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:40,417
On Track A, the Trans Europe Express
Mistral is about to depart.

154
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,708
Please board the train.

155
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,250
Hello, Hélène?

156
00:10:48,958 --> 00:10:49,833
Darling,

157
00:10:49,917 --> 00:10:51,667
I'm calling from the train station.

158
00:10:52,542 --> 00:10:53,375
Yes.

159
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:56,708
No, not for long.

160
00:10:56,792 --> 00:10:57,625
No.

161
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:59,375
I have to do some writing,

162
00:10:59,458 --> 00:11:01,917
and I wanted to finish my book
before our wedding.

163
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:06,333
But you know I can only work
when I'm on the move.

164
00:11:06,417 --> 00:11:07,583
Traveling inspires me.

165
00:11:09,375 --> 00:11:12,833
Well, me, too, darling,
I can't wait to be married either.

166
00:11:13,375 --> 00:11:14,708
Listen,

167
00:11:14,792 --> 00:11:17,417
I'll call you back
because my train is leaving.

168
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:18,333
Love you.

169
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:20,750
See you-- goodbye.

170
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:04,458
Clara,

171
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:06,542
that's a pretty name.

172
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:11,708
Actually, maybe pretty
isn't the right word,

173
00:12:11,792 --> 00:12:13,458
but it's a name that's--

174
00:12:13,542 --> 00:12:14,500
Clear!

175
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:15,542
Yes.

176
00:12:19,292 --> 00:12:21,208
It's funny how big the countryside is.

177
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:25,708
It's even too big, if you think about it.

178
00:12:28,917 --> 00:12:31,625
I wonder why the countryside is so big.

179
00:12:31,708 --> 00:12:34,500
That's a question I've never asked myself.

180
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,792
It's funny, I always ask
questions no one else does.

181
00:12:38,875 --> 00:12:39,708
Why?

182
00:12:40,542 --> 00:12:41,583
I wonder why.

183
00:12:42,292 --> 00:12:43,917
-Because you're curious.
-Oh no.

184
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:45,917
-No?

185
00:12:47,417 --> 00:12:49,458
For a woman, I'm not curious at all.

186
00:12:49,542 --> 00:12:51,792
-Oh really?
-But I'm interested in everything.

187
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:55,833
I always want to know
how things will turn out.

188
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,625
Would you like a cigarette?

189
00:12:59,625 --> 00:13:01,292
No thanks, I don't smoke.

190
00:13:01,375 --> 00:13:02,667
But I'll still have one.

191
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,958
Usually, you can only smoke one.

192
00:13:08,417 --> 00:13:09,250
That's true.

193
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:13,833
I wonder why.

194
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:19,792
I like to put two or three chocolates
in my mouth at the same time.

195
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:22,042
Luckily, I never eat them.

196
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:24,750
-Why?
-Because I hate it.

197
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:27,792
I hate anything sweet.

198
00:13:29,125 --> 00:13:30,500
Except for cake, of course.

199
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,833
Forgive me for intruding.

200
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:38,708
Sir, if you could sign this menu for me,

201
00:13:38,792 --> 00:13:40,208
I'll paste it in your book.

202
00:13:40,292 --> 00:13:41,125
My pleasure.

203
00:13:44,292 --> 00:13:46,667
-Here you are.
-I've read all your books.

204
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:47,833
Really?

205
00:13:47,917 --> 00:13:49,292
Why do you write books?

206
00:13:49,917 --> 00:13:51,417
Why shouldn't I write them?

207
00:13:53,542 --> 00:13:55,792
Because there are
so many other things to do.

208
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:58,500
I knew a writer once.

209
00:13:59,708 --> 00:14:00,542
Which one?

210
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:03,417
I forgot his name.

211
00:14:03,792 --> 00:14:05,292
He was a great chess player.

212
00:14:05,375 --> 00:14:06,792
Do you play chess?

213
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:08,875
Do I look like I play chess?

214
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:10,292
What's your sign?

215
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:12,000
Aries.

216
00:14:12,083 --> 00:14:13,167
I should have known.

217
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:14,833
I'm a Libra.

218
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:16,375
Alcohol, liqueur?

219
00:14:17,542 --> 00:14:18,667
No, thank you.

220
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,417
We'll have a drink while working.

221
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,417
I hope you don't mind getting to work.

222
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,167
Did a woman give you that tie?

223
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:28,083
Yes.

224
00:14:29,542 --> 00:14:30,375
Why?

225
00:14:31,667 --> 00:14:33,083
Because it doesn't suit you.

226
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:07,292
Put The Women as the title.

227
00:15:14,208 --> 00:15:15,042
Very good.

228
00:15:16,042 --> 00:15:17,417
Start a new paragraph.

229
00:15:20,417 --> 00:15:21,792
"How I got here."

230
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:25,667
Type!

231
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,542
It's the title of the first chapter.

232
00:15:28,542 --> 00:15:29,500
"How I got here."

233
00:15:31,583 --> 00:15:34,458
"Next week, I'm marrying
Marianne in St. Moritz

234
00:15:34,542 --> 00:15:36,000
and Hélène in Venice."

235
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:36,958
Period, new line.

236
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,542
You or your character?

237
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:41,583
Me.

238
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:42,500
Is that true?

239
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,292
Yes.

240
00:15:44,375 --> 00:15:45,458
How funny.

241
00:15:45,542 --> 00:15:48,583
"For 15 years, I've written
only about women,

242
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:51,333
and I'm interested in only them."

243
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:55,167
I've always dreamed of seeing up close
a man who never loved.

244
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:56,583
Right.

245
00:15:57,625 --> 00:16:00,083
It's precisely because I loved
that I was loved...

246
00:16:01,667 --> 00:16:03,333
and that I wrote my first book.

247
00:16:05,083 --> 00:16:08,083
My first book was inspired
by a broken heart,

248
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,167
a break-up

249
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:12,333
that I didn't intend.

250
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:16,625
The first woman who mattered in my life

251
00:16:17,417 --> 00:16:18,708
was named Anne.

252
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:21,625
We liked the same things,

253
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:23,958
including freedom,

254
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:25,542
which is so rare.

255
00:16:27,375 --> 00:16:28,417
We were happy...

256
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,542
because we had the same tastes,

257
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:33,958
the same education,

258
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:36,458
the same desires.

259
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:38,708
In short,

260
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:40,625
we got along swimmingly.

261
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:44,208
We never left each other.

262
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:51,167
And yet, we were as free as the first day.

263
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:54,583
Everything was perfect between us.

264
00:16:56,667 --> 00:16:57,958
Never a moment of boredom.

265
00:16:59,917 --> 00:17:01,833
We also loved to talk,

266
00:17:03,292 --> 00:17:04,292
to make love,

267
00:17:05,625 --> 00:17:06,542
and to be silent.

268
00:17:08,042 --> 00:17:09,250
It was--

269
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,167
Happiness?

270
00:17:11,375 --> 00:17:14,250
"At any rate, it looked like happiness.”
Period, new line.

271
00:17:15,292 --> 00:17:16,333
How long did it last?

272
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:19,750
It lasted...

273
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:22,750
Five years.

274
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:23,792
What's five years?

275
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:26,167
Us.

276
00:17:27,417 --> 00:17:28,250
Listen...

277
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,708
you're leaving to Cuba for your report.

278
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:35,042
I'm going to San Francisco for my exhibit.

279
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:38,167
The Azores are on the way.

280
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:43,333
It'd be fun to get married there,
while we're at it.

