You have suffered.

861
01:04:26,250 --> 01:04:27,083
I like that.

862
01:04:28,792 --> 01:04:30,000
What about Marianne?

863
01:04:30,833 --> 01:04:33,333
How did you end up
wanting to marry her after that?

864
01:04:34,833 --> 01:04:38,542
First, I had my fill
of Hélène and her wedding,

865
01:04:38,625 --> 01:04:40,250
so I managed to postpone it.

866
01:04:40,333 --> 01:04:41,167
I was resigned.

867
01:04:41,875 --> 01:04:45,292
But I managed to postpone the date
and move the location.

868
01:04:46,292 --> 01:04:49,292
I was like a prisoner in his cell
who is no longer tormented

869
01:04:49,375 --> 01:04:51,083
and says, "That's the way it is."

870
01:04:51,167 --> 01:04:53,500
Put yourself in a prisoner's shoes.

871
01:04:54,833 --> 01:04:56,500
He's used to a certain routine,

872
01:04:57,125 --> 01:04:58,083
then suddenly...

873
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:01,417
something happens, an unexpected event.

874
01:05:01,500 --> 01:05:03,667
Not necessarily something
that sets him free

875
01:05:03,750 --> 01:05:05,917
or leads to his pardon or escape.

876
01:05:06,708 --> 01:05:07,667
Something...

877
01:05:08,500 --> 01:05:09,375
a noise...

878
01:05:10,417 --> 01:05:11,250
a smell...

879
01:05:12,333 --> 01:05:13,167
an event.

880
01:05:14,500 --> 01:05:16,417
For a prisoner, that event

881
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:18,333
gives him hope.

882
01:05:18,875 --> 01:05:20,167
And that event for me

883
01:05:20,708 --> 01:05:22,208
was Marianne's phone call.

884
01:05:23,125 --> 01:05:24,333
It jolted me awake.

885
01:05:24,417 --> 01:05:25,458
She was in Megéve.

886
01:05:27,458 --> 01:05:29,000
She wanted to see me.

887
01:05:29,083 --> 01:05:30,333
She had to see me.

888
01:05:31,250 --> 01:05:32,750
Naturally, she didn't say why.

889
01:05:32,833 --> 01:05:34,750
Marianne never says why.

890
01:05:37,417 --> 01:05:38,542
I imagined her.

891
01:05:38,625 --> 01:05:39,458
I saw her.

892
01:05:41,167 --> 01:05:43,083
I heard her voice and saw her body.

893
01:05:46,250 --> 01:05:49,667
No other woman could inflame
my imagination like her.

894
01:05:51,333 --> 01:05:52,583
I wanted to be near her.

895
01:05:53,208 --> 01:05:54,750
I was as impatient as she was.

896
01:05:55,917 --> 01:05:58,167
I imagined her hanging up the phone,

897
01:05:59,958 --> 01:06:02,667
and I leapt towards her body...

898
01:06:05,792 --> 01:06:07,750
her body that I could never forget

899
01:06:08,958 --> 01:06:11,250
because her soul...

900
01:06:12,083 --> 01:06:13,792
was a mystery to me.

901
01:06:15,917 --> 01:06:19,042
The mere memory of Marianne's body...

902
01:06:20,750 --> 01:06:23,417
was enough to drive me insane.

903
01:06:23,500 --> 01:06:26,292
I felt elation in her presence.

904
01:06:27,000 --> 01:06:28,875
The idea of seeing her made me feel...

905
01:06:31,875 --> 01:06:33,667
the promise of happiness,

906
01:06:34,458 --> 01:06:36,958
which I hadn't known before meeting her.

907
01:06:39,542 --> 01:06:40,792
She made me more intense.

908
01:06:44,958 --> 01:06:46,000
I was beside myself.

909
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:17,542
-You're ridiculous.
-Not at all.

910
01:07:17,625 --> 01:07:20,167
He's the first man
who makes me want to be faithful.

911
01:07:20,250 --> 01:07:21,958
Really? Well...

912
01:07:22,958 --> 01:07:23,792
Perfect.

913
01:07:24,417 --> 01:07:26,750
It was that good
on the boat in St. Tropez?

914
01:07:27,458 --> 01:07:28,292
Tell me.

915
01:07:28,375 --> 01:07:30,500
-No, I don't want to.
-Yes, tell me.

916
01:07:30,583 --> 01:07:31,417
No.

917
01:07:33,875 --> 01:07:34,750
Leave me alone.

918
01:07:50,083 --> 01:07:51,125
I questioned her.

919
01:07:52,250 --> 01:07:55,125
The guy was a pleasure boat king.

920
01:07:55,208 --> 01:07:57,292
He sailed from one marina to another.

921
01:07:57,375 --> 01:07:58,833
He was currently in America.

922
01:07:59,583 --> 01:08:01,250
He phoned three times a day.

923
01:08:01,333 --> 01:08:03,917
He sent 10 telegrams and long letters.

924
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:07,417
He took lessons to perfect
his French and Swedish.

925
01:08:07,500 --> 01:08:08,333
He was crazy.

926
01:08:08,750 --> 01:08:10,083
And so was I.

927
01:08:11,917 --> 01:08:13,083
Tell me!

928
01:08:13,167 --> 01:08:14,042
I don't want to.

929
01:08:15,333 --> 01:08:16,458
-Tell me.

930
01:08:18,500 --> 01:08:19,958
Leave me alone.

931
01:08:22,292 --> 01:08:23,125
Tell me!

932
01:08:23,708 --> 01:08:25,167
Tell me what it was like.

933
01:08:25,958 --> 01:08:26,792
No.

934
01:08:29,292 --> 01:08:30,125
Slut.

935
01:08:37,167 --> 01:08:39,333
He'd go crazy if he saw you here.

936
01:08:40,667 --> 01:08:42,167
But he doesn't see me.

937
01:08:42,250 --> 01:08:44,083
-Luckily.
-No, not luckily.

938
01:08:45,292 --> 01:08:47,333
When I left you in St. Tropez, I knew it.

939
01:08:48,333 --> 01:08:49,500
He must know too.

940
01:08:51,125 --> 01:08:52,125
You're crazy.

941
01:08:56,250 --> 01:08:58,000
Maybe you want me to call him.

942
01:08:59,125 --> 01:08:59,958
Yes.

943
01:09:12,083 --> 01:09:13,042
I had an idea.

944
01:09:14,500 --> 01:09:15,792
I became obsessed with it.

945
01:09:17,000 --> 01:09:18,667
I would tell her what I wanted...

946
01:09:19,667 --> 01:09:20,708
to bring him back.

947
01:09:21,792 --> 01:09:23,542
He was in the Bahamas or somewhere.

948
01:09:25,458 --> 01:09:27,542
She should have him come back urgently...

949
01:09:28,542 --> 01:09:29,875
the following day.

950
01:09:29,958 --> 01:09:30,958
Under what pretext?

951
01:09:32,458 --> 01:09:33,458
A good pretext.

952
01:09:36,042 --> 01:09:37,708
The truth but slightly altered.

953
01:09:39,667 --> 01:09:42,792
I wanted her to tell him
she met a man in Megéve

954
01:09:42,875 --> 01:09:44,083
who held her very close

955
01:09:44,167 --> 01:09:46,542
and whom she felt
she could no longer resist.

956
01:09:47,958 --> 01:09:49,875
And if he didn't come the next day,

957
01:09:50,583 --> 01:09:52,042
she feared what would happen.

958
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:54,375
She was asking for help.

959
01:09:54,458 --> 01:09:55,542
Did she refuse?

960
01:09:55,625 --> 01:09:56,875
Yes, she refused.

961
01:10:03,083 --> 01:10:06,125
It was time for his morning call
from wherever he was.

962
01:10:11,667 --> 01:10:12,500
Hello?

963
01:10:13,333 --> 01:10:14,167
Is it you?

964
01:10:17,708 --> 01:10:19,042
It snowed all last night.

965
01:10:21,375 --> 01:10:23,000
You can't imagine how cold it is.

966
01:10:26,208 --> 01:10:27,042
What?

967
01:10:28,292 --> 01:10:29,333
Your chest is bare?

968
01:10:30,750 --> 01:10:32,125
You're making me fantasize.

969
01:10:33,042 --> 01:10:35,625
-Your bare chest.
-Marianne, please.

970
01:10:38,333 --> 01:10:40,708
Darling, my skiing
is improving thanks to you.

971
01:10:41,583 --> 01:10:43,958
You said you wanted me
to be a great skier.

972
01:10:46,958 --> 01:10:47,792
Marianne.

973
01:10:49,292 --> 01:10:51,750
If you don't do it, I'll leave right now.

974
01:10:53,250 --> 01:10:55,333
I didn't read the letters the day before.

975
01:10:56,333 --> 01:10:57,958
I read both yesterday afternoon.

976
01:11:00,458 --> 01:11:02,500
I read both of them.

977
01:11:02,583 --> 01:11:03,708
They were delightful.

978
01:11:06,792 --> 01:11:08,292
If you do it, I'll marry you.

979
01:11:10,375 --> 01:11:11,417
If you do it...

980
01:11:12,250 --> 01:11:13,292
I'll marry you.

981
01:11:20,250 --> 01:11:21,083
Bob...

982
01:11:21,792 --> 01:11:23,250
I have something to tell you.

983
01:11:26,000 --> 01:11:27,542
It all went the way you wanted.

984
01:11:28,917 --> 01:11:30,250
He came the next day.

985
01:11:31,042 --> 01:11:34,750
There's always a gap
between a dream and its fulfillment.

986
01:11:34,833 --> 01:11:37,458
But it was small,
and he came two days later.

987
01:11:37,542 --> 01:11:38,917
I prepared everything.

988
01:11:39,000 --> 01:11:40,667
I booked a room in a new hotel.

989
01:11:41,250 --> 01:11:43,083
He came in and saw us...

990
01:11:43,667 --> 01:11:45,000
Making love?

991
01:11:45,083 --> 01:11:45,917
Yes.

992
01:11:48,625 --> 01:11:50,292
Who will you marry in the end?

993
01:11:50,958 --> 01:11:51,792
Neither.

994
01:11:52,417 --> 01:11:53,792
They're interconnected.

995
01:11:53,875 --> 01:11:56,417
I loved one because
of the other and vice-versa.

996
01:11:57,042 --> 01:11:58,750
It would be a crime to choose.

997
01:12:00,250 --> 01:12:01,833
You need a third.

998
01:12:03,625 --> 01:12:04,458
I have her.

999
01:12:06,333 --> 01:12:07,167
Why not?

1000
01:12:08,667 --> 01:12:10,708
Because I don't love you.

1001
01:12:11,750 --> 01:12:13,167
I don't love you either.

1002
01:12:14,333 --> 01:12:15,917
I have a taste for you.

1003
01:12:16,000 --> 01:12:17,083
It's delicious.

1004
01:12:18,458 --> 01:12:20,208
What you want is my help.

1005
01:12:21,750 --> 01:12:23,042
That's how men are today.

1006
01:12:23,583 --> 01:12:25,583
You have to help them without listening.

1007
01:12:27,167 --> 01:12:29,333
I hate being useful.

1008
01:12:30,583 --> 01:12:31,708
I don't want to.

1009
01:12:33,875 --> 01:12:36,417
Forgive me, I forgot about the contract.

1010
01:12:36,500 --> 01:12:38,917
I don't care about the contract,
I'll rip it up.

1011
01:12:40,250 --> 01:12:42,458
-Rip it up?
-Yes, I want you to want me.

1012
01:12:44,417 --> 01:12:45,542
But I don't want you.

1013
01:12:51,208 --> 01:12:52,208
Hello?

1014
01:12:52,292 --> 01:12:53,125
Yes.

1015
01:12:54,875 --> 01:12:55,917
A female journalist?

1016
01:12:57,333 --> 01:12:58,167
Oh really?

1017
01:12:59,417 --> 01:13:01,542
Is she-- well, is she...

1018
01:13:02,125 --> 01:13:04,333
is she young and pretty?

1019
01:13:05,667 --> 01:13:06,708
Okay, well...

1020
01:13:08,167 --> 01:13:09,208
Tell her to come up.

1021
01:13:19,583 --> 01:13:20,875
My dear Clara, I...

1022
01:13:22,792 --> 01:13:24,458
You want me to take a walk?

1023
01:13:24,542 --> 01:13:25,417
You understand.

1024
01:14:09,958 --> 01:14:13,083
-Some water?
-What? No... yes.

1025
01:14:13,167 --> 01:14:14,167
No, thank you.

1026
01:14:14,250 --> 01:14:17,208
The Algerian War, the Vietnam War,
the Nigerian Civil War...

1027
01:14:18,833 --> 01:14:19,958
-Do you want ice?
-No.

1028
01:14:23,333 --> 01:14:26,208
Suez... Budapest--

1029
01:14:26,292 --> 01:14:28,583
Yes, that's right,
Suez, Budapest, Prague.

1030
01:14:28,667 --> 01:14:30,333
Famine in Africa and Asia.

1031
01:14:30,417 --> 01:14:32,875
You know I'm not really to blame.

1032
01:14:32,958 --> 01:14:35,208
The Israeli problem, the Black problem...

1033
01:14:36,250 --> 01:14:38,958
You think due to 15 years of writing,
these disasters--

1034
01:14:39,042 --> 01:14:41,375
None of these problems matter to you.

1035
01:14:41,458 --> 01:14:44,208
The conflict between neo-capitalism
and neo-Marxism,

1036
01:14:44,292 --> 01:14:46,917
decolonization, protest, youth,

1037
01:14:47,000 --> 01:14:49,750
overpopulation,
which will become horrible in 20 years

1038
01:14:49,833 --> 01:14:51,958
since the global population will double

1039
01:14:52,042 --> 01:14:55,542
and automation will have relegated
half of humankind to unemployment.

1040
01:14:55,625 --> 01:14:57,167
Where did you get your glasses?

1041
01:14:57,875 --> 01:15:00,500
Rather than taking on
the issues of your time,

1042
01:15:00,583 --> 01:15:03,083
you've wasted your time on women.

1043
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:06,917
Today's woman is a monumental problem.

1044
01:15:07,417 --> 01:15:09,667
She claims to be both free and oppressed,

1045
01:15:10,250 --> 01:15:12,375
capricious and conventional,

1046
01:15:12,458 --> 01:15:14,292
man's equal and his dependent.

1047
01:15:15,042 --> 01:15:17,417
It's safer to take an interest in politics

1048
01:15:17,500 --> 01:15:18,792
rather than modern women.

1049
01:15:19,708 --> 01:15:20,542
Tell me...

1050
01:15:21,417 --> 01:15:22,333
what's your name?

1051
01:15:22,917 --> 01:15:23,750
Louise.

1052
01:15:27,667 --> 01:15:29,292
Tell me, Louise, your glasses...

1053
01:15:31,292 --> 01:15:33,125
Some glasses make eyes bigger.

1054
01:15:34,583 --> 01:15:36,250
I'm sure yours make them smaller.

1055
01:15:37,083 --> 01:15:38,250
How do you know that?

1056
01:15:40,542 --> 01:15:41,375
May 1?

1057
01:15:45,500 --> 01:15:46,667
Oh yes.

1058
01:15:47,750 --> 01:15:49,500
I was right.

1059
01:15:49,583 --> 01:15:52,042
Of course, I knew it.

1060
01:15:54,208 --> 01:15:55,625
I liked you from the start.

1061
01:15:57,250 --> 01:15:58,417
I don't even know why.

1062
01:16:01,042 --> 01:16:02,417
There are two women in you.

1063
01:16:05,500 --> 01:16:07,250
First of all, I don't love him.

1064
01:16:07,333 --> 01:16:10,583
Secondly, if I love him,
that's precisely why I shouldn't go back.

1065
01:16:11,292 --> 01:16:12,750
Third of all, he's a bastard.

1066
01:16:14,750 --> 01:16:18,792
Fourth of all, if I love him,
and I go back, I'll be unhappy.

1067
01:16:19,708 --> 01:16:22,750
Fifth of all, I shouldn't go back
if I don't love him,

1068
01:16:22,833 --> 01:16:24,625
and I shouldn't go back if I do.

1069
01:16:24,708 --> 01:16:25,708
It's the same thing.

1070
01:16:42,708 --> 01:16:45,083
Sixth of all, if I don't go back,

1071
01:16:45,750 --> 01:16:47,458
will that idiot leave me alone?

1072
01:16:49,458 --> 01:16:52,167
Seventh of all,
if I don't go back, I'll be unhappy.

1073
01:16:52,250 --> 01:16:53,958
I'll be unhappy no matter what.

1074
01:16:56,708 --> 01:17:00,583
Eighth of all, I'm prepared to be unhappy
whether or not I stay with him.

1075
01:17:01,917 --> 01:17:05,333
Ninth of all, I'll be unhappy
for longer if I stay with him

1076
01:17:05,750 --> 01:17:07,125
because I love him.

1077
01:17:12,042 --> 01:17:12,958
It's very simple.

1078
01:17:13,750 --> 01:17:15,125
First of all, I'll tell her

1079
01:17:15,667 --> 01:17:17,292
I was ridiculous with the girl

1080
01:17:17,375 --> 01:17:21,042
because I couldn't stop thinking of you
and couldn't do anything with her.

1081
01:17:21,125 --> 01:17:23,917
Second of all,
why couldn't I do anything with her?

1082
01:17:24,667 --> 01:17:26,750
Because her only flaw was she wasn't you.

1083
01:17:26,833 --> 01:17:27,958
That's where we are.

1084
01:17:28,042 --> 01:17:28,917
I love you.

1085
01:17:58,750 --> 01:17:59,667
Are you mad at me?

1086
01:18:00,833 --> 01:18:01,667
I don't care.

1087
01:18:04,125 --> 01:18:05,250
I tried to forget you.

1088
01:18:06,875 --> 01:18:07,833
I failed.

1089
01:18:12,500 --> 01:18:13,333
What?

1090
01:18:13,833 --> 01:18:15,667
I tried to forget you and failed.

1091
01:18:17,875 --> 01:18:19,292
That girl had only one flaw.

1092
01:18:20,167 --> 01:18:21,042
She wasn't you.

1093
01:18:25,083 --> 01:18:25,917
Bastard.

1094
01:18:28,250 --> 01:18:29,083
I told her...

1095
01:18:30,292 --> 01:18:31,125
I love Clara.

1096
01:18:37,458 --> 01:18:38,792
You don't love Clara.

1097
01:18:39,667 --> 01:18:40,875
You love women.

1098
01:20:56,917 --> 01:20:57,750
Help!

1099
01:20:58,500 --> 01:20:59,333
Help!

1100
01:21:42,000 --> 01:21:43,125
You're here.

1101
01:21:43,208 --> 01:21:44,292
You're here for real.

1102
01:21:45,500 --> 01:21:46,333
I'm saved.

1103
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:47,875
